************************************************************
If you want to use the Kerberos 4 r-commands or su, you will
need to run the following command as root:

  # chmod u+s %%PREFIX%%/bin/rsh
  # chmod u+s %%PREFIX%%/bin/rcp
  # chmod u+s %%PREFIX%%/bin/rlogin
  # chmod u+s %%PREFIX%%/bin/su
************************************************************
